            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "> > before [9f90992](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/9f909929344287bc1246d6b4dab55d500b514396) the windows ti defs would just get cleared.\r\n> \r\n> I can't reproduce that (neither with my revert nor with `git checkout 9f90992934^`).\r\n\r\nOkay, I can reproduce with 6.0.20150810¹:\r\n\r\n```console\r\n$ LD_LIBRARY_PATH=\"/tmp/nvim-old-ncurses\" PATH=/tmp/nvim-old-ncurses:\"$PATH\" nvim -ll src/gen/gen_terminfo.lua\r\ncurl -O https://invisible-island.net/datafiles/current/terminfo.src.gz\r\n  % Total    % Received % Xferd  Average Speed  Time    Time    Time   Current\r\n                                 Dload  Upload  Total   Spent   Left   Speed\r\n100 366.3k 100 366.3k   0      0  2.49M      0                              0\r\ngunzip -f terminfo.src.gz\r\ncat terminfo.src scripts/windows.ti | tic -x -o \"/tmp/nvim_terminfo\" -\r\n\"<stdin>\", line 4096, terminal 'scrt': error writing /tmp/nvim_terminfo/s/scrt\r\nrm -f terminfo.src\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/i/interix.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/p/putty-256color.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/r/rxvt-256color.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/s/screen-256color.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/s/st-256color.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/t/tmux-256color.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/v/vte-256color.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/x/xterm-256color.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/c/cygwin.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/w/win32con.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/c/conemu.\r\ninfocmp: couldn't open terminfo file /tmp/nvim_terminfo/v/vtpcon.\r\n```\r\n\r\nSeems to me that `tic` chokes on line 4096, terminal 'scrt' for whatever reason…\r\n\r\nThe fix doesn't help though :-D\r\n\r\n¹) https://snapshot.debian.org/archive/debian/20150817T213310Z/pool/main/n/ncurses/ncurses-bin_6.0%2B20150810-1_amd64.deb, https://snapshot.debian.org/archive/debian/20150817T213310Z/pool/main/n/ncurses/libtinfo5_6.0%2B20150810-1_amd64.deb, extract a few files, set LD_LIBRARY_PATH and PATH",
